tst.test("[TOOL_CALLS][{\"name\": \"special_function\", \"arguments\": {\"arg1\": 1}, \"id\": \"123456789\"}]")
    .tools({ special_function_tool })
    .expect(message_assist_call_id)
    .expect_reconstruction()
    .run();
```

Add parallel tool calls test after the existing ones:
```cpp
tst.test("[TOOL_CALLS][{\"name\": \"special_function\", \"arguments\": {\"arg1\": 1}, \"id\": \"123456789\"}, "
         "{\"name\": \"special_function\", \"arguments\": {\"arg1\": 2}, \"id\": \"987654321\"}]")
    .parallel_tool_calls(true)
    .tools({ special_function_tool })
    .expect_tool_calls({
        { "special_function", R"({"arg1": 1})", "123456789" },
        { "special_function", R"({"arg1": 2})", "987654321" },
    })
    .expect_reconstruction()
    .run();
```

## Verification

```bash
# Build the test targets
cmake --build build --target test-chat -j
cmake --build build --target test-chat-template -j

# Run chat tests (includes PEG parser tests for Nemo template)
./build/bin/test-chat 2>&1 | grep -E "(PASS|FAIL|Nemo|mistral)"

# Run template tests against the Nemo Jinja file
./build/bin/test-chat-template models/templates/mistralai-Mistral-Nemo-Instruct-2407.jinja

# Run full automated template test suite
./build/bin/test-chat-template
```

Key things to verify:
1. Existing Nemo tests pass (content-only + single tool call + reconstruction)
2. New parallel tool call test passes
3. Ministral 3 handler still triggers for its template (regression check)
4. No other templates are accidentally captured by the new detection

