# Plan: Add "mistral-instruct-v3" Specialized Chat Template Handler

## Context

Mistral Instruct v0.3 models (e.g., Mistral-Nemo-Instruct-2407) use a chat format with `[INST]`/`[/INST]` user turn markers, system messages prepended inline to the first user turn, and `</s>` after assistant turns. These templates currently fall through to the autoparser in the Jinja path. This change adds a dedicated specialized handler for better control over parsing, specifically for tool call handling in the `[TOOL_CALLS][{...}]` JSON array format.

The handler must be distinguished from the existing Ministral 3 handler (which uses `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` + `[ARGS]` markers) by checking for the **absence** of `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]`.

**Constraint:** Only add new code — do not modify any existing handlers or the header file (`src/llama-chat.h`).

## Files to Modify

| File | Change |
|------|--------|
| `common/chat.cpp` | Add new `common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3()` function + detection block |
| `tests/test-chat.cpp` | Add/expand test cases for the new handler |

Files NOT modified (per constraint): `src/llama-chat.h`, `src/llama-chat.cpp`, existing handler functions.

## Step 1: Add `common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3()` function

**File:** `common/chat.cpp`  
**Location:** Insert immediately before `common_chat_try_specialized_template()` (before line 1634), following the pattern of other init functions defined above the dispatcher.

The function follows the same structure as `common_chat_params_init_ministral_3()` (line 825) but is simpler — no reasoning/thinking support needed.

**Key design decisions:**
- Use `p.standard_json_tools()` (from `common_chat_peg_builder`, declared at `common/chat-peg-parser.h:108`) to parse the `[TOOL_CALLS][{"name": "...", "arguments": {...}, "id": "..."}]` JSON array format. This is the correct utility for standard JSON-based tool calls.
- Parameters for `standard_json_tools`: `section_start="[TOOL_CALLS]"`, `section_end=""`, `name_key="name"`, `args_key="arguments"`, `array_wrapped=true`, `call_id_key="id"`.
- `supports_thinking = false` — no `[THINK]`/`[/THINK]` markers in this format.
- `preserved_tokens = {"[TOOL_CALLS]"}` — prevent tokenizer from splitting the marker.
- Use `common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl(tmpl, inputs)` to render the prompt via the Jinja template (line 767).
- Grammar trigger on `"[TOOL_CALLS]"` for lazy grammar activation.

**Function skeleton:**
```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template &          tmpl,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    common_chat_params data;
    auto has_tools       = inputs.tools.is_array() && !inputs.tools.empty();
    auto include_grammar = true;

    data.prompt            = common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl(tmpl, inputs);
    data.format            = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_PEG_NATIVE;
    data.supports_thinking = false;
    data.preserved_tokens  = { "[TOOL_CALLS]" };

    auto parser = build_chat_peg_parser([&](common_chat_peg_builder & p) {
        auto generation_prompt = p.prefix(inputs.generation_prompt);

        // JSON schema response format
        if (inputs.json_schema.is_object() && !inputs.json_schema.empty()) {
            return generation_prompt << p.content(
                p.schema(p.json(), "response-format", inputs.json_schema));
        }

        // Tool calls: [TOOL_CALLS][{"name": ..., "arguments": {...}, "id": "..."}]
        if (has_tools && inputs.tool_choice != COMMON_CHAT_TOOL_CHOICE_NONE) {
            auto tool_calls = p.standard_json_tools(
                /* section_start      */ "[TOOL_CALLS]",
                /* section_end        */ "",
                /* tools              */ inputs.tools,
                /* parallel           */ inputs.parallel_tool_calls,
                /* force              */ inputs.tool_choice == COMMON_CHAT_TOOL_CHOICE_REQUIRED,
                /* name_key           */ "name",
                /* args_key           */ "arguments",
                /* array_wrapped      */ true,
                /* function_is_key    */ false,
                /* call_id_key        */ "id");

            return generation_prompt + (p.content(p.until("[TOOL_CALLS]")) << tool_calls);
        }

        // Content only
        include_grammar = false;
        return generation_prompt << p.content(p.rest());
    });

    data.parser = parser.save();

    if (include_grammar) {
        data.grammar_lazy = has_tools && inputs.tool_choice == COMMON_CHAT_TOOL_CHOICE_AUTO;
        data.grammar = build_grammar([&](const common_grammar_builder & builder) {
            foreach_function(inputs.tools, [&](const json & tool) {
                auto schema = tool.at("function").at("parameters");
                builder.resolve_refs(schema);
            });
            parser.build_grammar(builder, data.grammar_lazy);
        });
        data.grammar_triggers = {
            { COMMON_GRAMMAR_TRIGGER_TYPE_WORD, "[TOOL_CALLS]" }
        };
    }

    return data;
}
```

